&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BIRMINGHAM COMMUNITY HEALTHCARE NHS FOUNDATION TRUST&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CHILDREN &amp; FAMILIES DIVISION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SPECIAL NEEDS NURSING&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Special Needs Nurse – BCHC Plus&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band 5&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;32.5 hours (09:30 to 16:30 Monday to Friday), term time only (39 weeks). (The post holder must be able to work one additional hour/day when requested, to a maximum of 37.5hrs per week)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the past 5 years BCHC’s Traded Services programme, BCHC Plus has become firmly established amongst Birmingham’s schools, enabling us to directly satisfy their need for additional services that supplement those provided under local health commissioning. With enviable customer feedback and a reputation for service excellence, interest in our traded programme remains strong amongst all schools.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We want to recruit a Band 5 Special Needs Nurse based in Victoria Specialist College to provide a bespoke health provision for students with complex health and learning needs and an age range of 19 – 25 years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The working hours are 32.5 hours per week (09:30 to 16:30 Monday to Friday) during school term time (39 weeks per annum)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome applications from experienced Adult or Learning Disabilities Trained Nurses who have proven experience of working with a wide range of Learning Disabilities and of working with young people with complex health needs and learning disability. A RNLD or RGN qualification is essential for this role as is evidence of continuing professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will implement and deliver the BCHC Plus special school nursing programme, to include specialist assessment and care planning; management of administration of medicine; provision of clinical care; safeguarding and support to education staff, parents and students.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate must have excellent communication skills and be able to manage his/her time effectively. An understanding of the needs of young adults with a disability and/or additional health problems is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Post holders may need to travel during the working day to support students on field trips, and be present on site at the start and end of the day when the pupils arrive and depart on transport.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Louise Proudlock, BCHC Plus School Nursing Team Leader on 0121 466 6266&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that this post will be capped and may close early, therefore early application is advised.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameLouise ProudlockJob titleBCHC Plus School Nurse Team LeaderEmail addresslouise.proudlock@bhamcommunity.nhs.ukTelephone number07545 419380&lt;/p&gt;
